Window Functions for Formulas

In CRM Analytics, use window functions in a Data Prep recipe to perform calculations across rows. For each row of input data, perform a calculation on a selection—or window—of related rows.

You can use the following window functions:
current(field)
dense_rank()
first_value(field)
lag(field)
last_value(field)
lead(field)
rank()
row_number()
sum()
collect_list(field)
collect_set(field)
title: Window Functions in CRM Analytics Formulas
